org.knime.core.data

Interface DataCellFactory

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataCellFactory.FromComplexString, DataCellFactory.FromInputStream, DataCellFactory.FromReader, DataCellFactory.FromSimpleString, DataCellFactory.FromString
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinaryObjectCellFactory, BooleanCell.BooleanCellFactory, DateAndTimeCellFactory, DenseBitVectorCell.Factory, DenseByteVectorCell.Factory, DoubleCell.DoubleCellFactory, FuzzyIntervalCell.FuzzyIntervallCellFactory, FuzzyNumberCell.FuzzyNumberCellFactory, IntCell.IntCellFactory, IntervalCell.IntervallCellFactory, LongCell.LongCellFactory, PMMLCellFactory, PNGImageCellFactory, SparseBitVectorCell.Factory, StringCell.StringCellFactory, XMLCellFactory

    public interface DataCellFactory
    Interface for a factory that can create data cells from certain input formats. The factory is free to create any compatible cell, e.g. normal or blob cell. Such factories are mainly used by reader node in order to create arbitrary cells based on the user-supplied node configuration. A new factory is created every time a node requests one via the DataType.getCellFactory(ExecutionContext).
    Note that you should not implement the DataCellFactory interface directly. Instead implement any of the sub-interfaces that read from a specific input source.
    Since:
    3.0
    Author:
    Thorsten Meinl, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

    • Method Detail

      • getDataType

        DataType getDataType()
        Returns the data type of the cells that this factory will create.
        Returns:
        a data type, never null

      • init

        default void init(ExecutionContext execContext)
        This method is called once by DataTypeRegistry when a factory instance is created. The default implementation does nothing but implementors can override it a make use of the passed execution context. Note that this method may not be called or called with a null argument. In this case it's allowed to fail when an attempt to create a cell is made and an execution context is required.
        Parameters:
        execContext - the current node's execution context, may be null
        No public API: not to be referenced by clients
        This method is not intended to be referenced by clients.
